race.comment: UNIVERSAL IMPACT (11) gave away a big start at the top of the straight last time and finished eighth over 1400m at Ascot. Well placed back in maiden company, and she is the one to beat. RAYLANA (9) was runner-up here when resuming, and then finished well back over 1200m at Ascot last time put. Stick with her here. COMMON TOUCH (1) is a promising maiden who finished fifth over 1200m at Ascot last time out, and he looks well suited in this field. He is among the main top four chances. JOYOH (8) has gone close with two straight placings, the latest a third over 1400m here, and she finds a nice race to post an overdue first win. COSMIC TREAT (10) finished a sound fifth at Bunbury when fresh, and is worth including in all top four combos here.
